to cross that bar in a storm like this.

574
00:51:45,726 --> 00:51:50,691
<i>Maybe they CAN turn back,</i>
maybe they get<i> lost BEFORE.

575
00:51:50,858 --> 00:51:52,451
Can't get out.

576
00:51:55,905 --> 00:51:58,013
You know Bernie, right?

577
00:51:59,233 --> 00:52:01,453
You know he won't
get lost out there.

578
00:52:02,829 --> 00:52:05,082
You know he follows the rules.

579
00:52:05,694 --> 00:52:08,146
Yeah, we know.

580
00:52:09,212 --> 00:52:13,926
We all going down to the pier soon,
<i>see if there's anything we can do down there.

581
00:52:17,263 --> 00:52:18,847
Welcome to come.

582
00:52:30,111 --> 00:52:32,363
Miriam, Miriam,
please come here.

583
00:52:32,563 --> 00:52:33,863
Miriam?

584
00:52:36,743 --> 00:52:39,831
- Excuse me, are you Commander Cluff?
- Who are you?

585
00:52:39,897 --> 00:52:43,310
I'm Miriam Pentinen, Bernie Webber's
girlfriend, I want you to call Bernie back in.

586
00:52:43,376 --> 00:52:46,378
The girl he was askin' me about,
do you know what he was gonna ask me?

587
00:52:46,839 --> 00:52:48,992
For your permission to marry me.

588
00:52:49,614 --> 00:52:51,547
Well, that's between you,
him and your god.

589
00:52:51,602 --> 00:52:54,471
<i>Asking me is just a formality,
he can marry</i> all he wants.

590
00:52:54,591 --> 00:52:57,871
Don't you know that?
But you can't be in here, Miss.

591
00:52:58,810 --> 00:52:59,810
It's Bernie.

592
00:53:00,253 --> 00:53:03,357
<i>- Chatham bar dead ahead. Over.
- 36-500, Station Chatham,

